<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-09-09T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-09-09T07:00:00-05:00" n="659" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d659">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">683.84A/9–953: Telegram</note>
                        <head>No. 659<lb/><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Syria (<persName corresp="#p_MJS1" type="from">Moose</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d659fn1">Repeated for information to Jerusalem and Tel
                                Aviv.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Damascus</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-09-09T14:00:00+02:00">September 9, 1953—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>82. Besides the danger of bloodshed if Israel is permitted to continue
                            work on project for diversion of remainder of Jordan waters reported in
                                <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 81, September 9,<note n="2" xml:id="d659fn2">Telegram 81 from Damascus, Sept. 9, reported
                                on the Israeli diversion of the Jordan River at Banat Yaacov.
                                (683.84A/9–953)</note> Syrian resentment can hinder or defeat any or
                            all of following projects advocated by US Government: <pb facs="1344" n="1304" xml:id="pg_1304"/>
                            <list>
                                <label>(1)</label>
                                <item>Division of Demilitarized Zone as step toward eventual
                                    Syro–Israeli peaceful relationship (cf. Embassy despatch 116,
                                    August 21).<note n="3" xml:id="d659fn3">Not
                                    printed.</note></item>
                                <label>(2)</label>
                                <item>Jordan-Yarmuk development plan referred to in <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 73, September 4.<note n="4" xml:id="d659fn4">Printed as telegram 316 to Beirut,
                                            <ref target="#d656">Document 656</ref>.</note></item>
                                <label>(3)</label>
                                <item>Any bilateral or multilateral defense arrangements implicit in
                                    prospective aid programs for Syria.</item>
                            </list></p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_MJS1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>